# Release Policy

- Ship from `main`. Do not keep release work on long-lived feature branches once it is ready.
- Use real release versions, even for versions that have not launched yet. If a release breaks, fix forward with the next real version.
- Desktop app releases in `senda-network/senda` use normal `vX.Y.Z` release tags/names. Do not create `desktop-v*` app release tags.
- Runtime releases in `senda-network/senda-llm` use normal `vX.Y.Z` versions with `prerelease=false`. Do not create `*-pre`, prerelease, or candidate runtime versions unless Al explicitly overrides this rule.
- Always scope GitHub CLI calls with `-R senda-network/senda` or `-R senda-network/senda-llm`.
